Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.16,0:00:41.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,This film contains very strong\nlanguage and some violent scenes
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.68,0:00:49.00,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice shot, Hamb.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.00,0:00:51.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I drilled a little\nto the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.40,0:00:53.60,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 15 feet\nfrom the goddamn hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.52,0:00:56.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I miscalculated the wind\nby a couple knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.84,0:00:57.92,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.92,0:01:00.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know,\nit's all a matter\nof degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.04,0:01:03.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,The difference between\nthe big money and not making\nthe cut is razor-thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.68,0:01:08.76,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I wasn't thinking about\nqualifying for the Masters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.76,0:01:11.60,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Kind of had my sights\nset on the NBA.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.60,0:01:15.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HELICOPTER WHIRRS OVERHEAD
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.44,0:01:24.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, your hook shot's\nworking, Scotty.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.08,0:01:41.56,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.76,0:01:49.72,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think\nI'm doing wrong here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.56,0:01:54.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you're standing\ntoo close to the ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.48,0:01:55.92,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.\nPretty bad, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.92,0:01:57.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,After you hit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.32,0:01:58.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,..Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.36,0:02:01.20,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,They want you at ops\nright away, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.32,0:04:22.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&}- MAN:{\r}\N- Russian tanks,\n8-inch guns, and APCs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.84,0:04:25.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Seventh Air Force intelligence\nhas been indicating
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.44,0:04:28.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,the possibility of\na North Vietnamese/VC offensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.12,0:04:30.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, these photos\nconfirm it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.48,0:04:35.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,NVA troops moving down\nthe Ho Chi Minh Trail,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.04,0:04:39.48,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,south of the DMZ,\nnear Quang Tri.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.48,0:04:41.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, they'll combine\nwith Charlie
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.24,0:04:44.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,and try to hit us hard,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.12,0:04:46.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,probably in several\nplaces at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.40,0:04:49.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Glad you could\nmake it, Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.40,0:04:51.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.16,0:04:55.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Strategic Air\nCommand's putting\neverything it's got
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.44,0:04:58.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,in the air two days from now\nand will just clobber\nthe hell out of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.44,0:05:00.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't stop\ntheir movement,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.76,0:05:03.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,or at least slow it down\nto a trickle,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.76,0:05:06.16,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,our ground troops\nare going to take\nheavy casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.16,0:05:08.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, our job\nremains the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.80,0:05:11.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,fly alongside\nthe bombers,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.64,0:05:13.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,throw down\nyour electronic\nsmoke screens,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.80,0:05:15.88,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,jam the missile radars.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.88,0:05:18.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, why don't we put\nour surveillance aircraft\nup there first, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.60,0:05:21.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Have them fly the same route\nthe big boys are going to fly\non their scheduled run.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.84,0:05:23.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Missile reaction\ncan be recorded,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.40,0:05:26.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,launch sites\nplotted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.36,0:05:29.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Send the fighter jocks\nin there to just knock\nthe hell out of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.04,0:05:48.52,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I really appreciate\nyou volunteering us\nfor this flight, Hamb.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.52,0:05:51.24,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't think you had\nyour sights set on\nbeing a full bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.24,0:05:53.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got my sights\nset on a condo
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.64,0:05:56.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,on the seventh fairway\nat Tucson National.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.52,0:05:59.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Six months from now,\nthat's where the old lady\nand me will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.40,0:06:01.80,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds\nawfully exciting(!)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.80,0:06:04.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You think\nthat's exciting?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.80,0:06:06.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You should see\nthe deck furniture.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.40,0:06:08.56,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.84,0:06:19.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark. Start your music.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.48,0:06:23.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got\na solid growl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.40,0:06:25.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,SAM on scope.\nI confirm a launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.68,0:06:27.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I got him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.80,0:06:34.40,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddamn it.\nI didn't think they had\nSAMs this far south.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.40,0:06:36.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.32,0:06:38.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Have to go back and\ngive them the bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.84,0:06:40.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.84,0:06:42.68,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,SAM on scope.\n2, salvo 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.68,0:06:46.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,They're changing frequencies.\nI've got one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.48,0:06:49.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it steady.\nGot two.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.40,0:06:51.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&HFFFF00&}- Got one visual.\n{\r}\N- Break left!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.24,0:06:53.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Break left!\nLOUD BUZZING
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.40,0:06:55.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,It's tracking us!\nIt's locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.84,0:07:03.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,We're hit!\nEverybody get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.24,0:07:05.36,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going down!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.36,0:07:06.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,We're burning up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.48,0:07:10.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Hit by SAM!\nMayday! Mayday!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.84,0:07:12.76,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I've lost it.\nCrew eject! Crew eject!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.76,0:07:14.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.44,0:07:17.08,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Red Scout One\nhit by SAMs!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.08,0:07:18.52,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Punch out, Hamb!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.52,0:07:19.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Scotty!\nLet's get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.96,0:07:21.36,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Right behind you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.36,0:07:22.52,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayday! Mayday!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.56,0:07:35.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Punch out, Scotty!\nSomebody punch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.24,0:07:52.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,RADIO: 'Recon pilots\nin quadrant Lima-Charlie-Six,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.08,0:07:55.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,'Mayday transmitted\nby Red Scout EB-66.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.84,0:07:57.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,'Look for smoke\nand chutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.04,0:07:59.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,'Repeat, look for smoke\nand chutes.'
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.44,0:08:00.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.04,0:08:07.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HAMBLETON ON RADIO: 02 FAC!\n02, come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.68,0:08:11.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,This is FAC 02,\ncall sign Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.40,0:08:13.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Identify yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.04,0:08:16.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Bat 21. I'm the\nparachute above you,\none o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.68,0:08:18.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,BEEPING
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.24,0:08:22.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you in sight.\nTurn off your beeper, Bat 21,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.60,0:08:25.36,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,or Charlie will get to you\nbefore the Jolly Greens.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.36,0:08:27.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Will advise.\nHappy landings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.60,0:08:29.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.00,0:09:11.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Bat 21, get out\nof that paddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.20,0:09:13.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Hooches to the south.\nHead north to the tree line.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.60,0:09:16.48,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Repeat, head north\nto the tree line.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.68,0:09:27.48,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Repeat, tree line\nnorth. Roger that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.48,0:09:29.88,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative.\nI want to wait\nfor the choppers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.88,0:09:31.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.24,0:09:33.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get the basic\nrelationship down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.24,0:09:36.88,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the lifeguard.\nYou're the drowning man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.88,0:09:39.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,If you relax, I can\nbring you to shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.24,0:09:41.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,If you fight me,\nthen I'll have to\nslap you around.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.40,0:09:43.48,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, get your ass\nin gear, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.76,0:09:55.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Bat 21, Charlie's firing\nmortars from the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.60,0:09:58.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Advise at tree line.\nRepeat, advise at tree line.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.52,0:10:50.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,PLANE APPROACHES
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.88,0:10:55.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, this is Bat 21.\nI can't go any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.12,0:10:56.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Get the helis\nfrom this position.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.64,0:10:59.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&H00FFFF&}- Copy, Bat 21.\n{\r}\N- What about the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.56,0:11:01.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Anybody else\nmake it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.16,0:11:03.88,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,None reported.\nWe're still looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.88,0:11:05.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Just stay calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.84,0:11:08.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.24,0:11:11.36,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, Bat 21.\nWe'll get you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.36,0:11:13.52,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not going\nto happen today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.52,0:11:16.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,All choppers busy\nevac-ing fire base\nat Quang Tri.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.44,0:11:18.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Company of guns\noverrun by Charlie.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.84,0:11:21.72,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Jolly Greens\nwill pick you up\nin the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.88,0:11:33.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Say again,\nyour last transmission.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.68,0:11:37.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Repeat, Jolly Greens\nwill pick you up\nin the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.96,0:11:41.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,There will be\nno pick-up today.\nCopy, Bat 21?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:43.76,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,EXPLOSIONS IN THE DISTANCE
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.20,0:11:47.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I copy, Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.08,0:11:49.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, listen, Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.04,0:11:53.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm running low on juice.\nHave to return to base.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.68,0:11:55.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, thanks\nfor your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.68,0:11:58.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what\nI'm here for.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.08,0:12:00.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, you\ngoing to be back?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.04,0:12:01.56,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.56,0:12:05.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog signing off.\nKeep your head down.\nSee you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.16,0:12:08.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Bat 21 out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.32,0:12:10.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,PLANE FADES INTO DISTANCE
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.00,0:12:37.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,THEY SPEAK IN VIETNAMESE
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.68,0:13:10.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,SITAR MUSIC PLAYS
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.36,0:13:15.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HE CHANTS
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.64,0:13:41.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,How was\nyour flight, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.68,0:13:46.48,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Same old shit,\nbad movies and terrible food.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.48,0:13:50.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you, uh...\ndon't you think
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.64,0:13:52.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,you're pushing it\na little, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.16,0:13:55.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You've almost doubled\nthe base record.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.56,0:13:57.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,The base record?\nSheesh!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.04,0:13:58.92,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pin a medal\non my chest(!)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.92,0:14:01.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you check\nmy right aileron?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.32,0:14:03.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,It's sticking\na bit, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.08,0:14:09.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I got to\nreplace it, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.04,0:14:11.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,How long\nwill that take?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.44,0:14:15.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I can borrow\none from 453.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.84,0:14:19.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Anderson's ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.00,0:14:21.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,The way he flies, Captain,\nhe'll never miss it, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.80,0:14:26.48,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha-ha-ha! I like\nyour initiative,\nSergeant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.48,0:14:28.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.76,0:14:32.44,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we've pulled\nour share of pilots\nout of there,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.44,0:14:34.84,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,but never\na 53-year-old\nLieutenant Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.84,0:14:38.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,A 53-year-old\nLieutenant Colonel?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.64,0:14:41.64,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.\nNavigator\non that EB.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.00,0:14:45.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,They just gave me\ncrew codes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.40,0:14:47.36,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,and no names\nand ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.36,0:14:50.28,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I am told\nthat Hambleton
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.28,0:14:51.68,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,is one of\nour top people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.68,0:14:53.56,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,He's an electronics\ncountermeasure\nexpert.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.56,0:14:56.32,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I am told\nthat the Communists
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.32,0:14:58.64,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,will have a dossier\non him that thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.64,0:15:01.12,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,So, in the morning,\nwhen we get\nour birds back,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.12,0:15:02.44,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,we're going to go in\nand get him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.44,0:15:04.12,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Seventh Air Force\ndoes not want Charlie
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.12,0:15:06.00,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,getting their hands\non him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.00,0:15:07.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll get him\ntomorrow then, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.96,0:15:09.40,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,In the meantime,\nI want you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.40,0:15:10.80,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,to go back\nout there tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.80,0:15:12.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's not going\nanywhere, Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.40,0:15:15.60,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, because I'm going\nto make damn certain\nhe's secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.60,0:15:17.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why don't you\nsend Anderson?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.00,0:15:19.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't he just get\nhis pilot's licence?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.44,0:15:21.84,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better\nwatch it, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.84,0:15:24.72,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, sir, I'm tired,\nI'm two weeks short,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.72,0:15:27.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,and that area\nis pretty hot,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.12,0:15:29.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,and I don't want\nto get shot down
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.00,0:15:31.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,on some public-relations\nmission, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.76,0:15:38.60,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, then,\nI'll make it easy\nfor you, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.60,0:15:41.40,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an order,\nand you damn well\nwill carry it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.40,0:15:43.44,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.16,0:15:47.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.56,0:15:55.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you\nfor the ride, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.40,0:16:53.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,TWIG SNAPS
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.96,0:17:56.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,MEN SPEAK SOFTLY IN VIETNAMESE
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.72,0:18:38.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,BRANCH SNAPS
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.88,0:19:30.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Phew! OK...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.36,0:19:32.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,50 piasters.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.28,0:19:33.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,THE OTHER MEN GROAN
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.72,0:19:35.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!\nChickenshits!\nChickenshits!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.64,0:19:37.08,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.08,0:19:39.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,OK. Hey, Clarky,\npull up a chair,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.00,0:19:40.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,before\nthese pigeons are\ntotally penniless.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.92,0:19:43.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Another time.\nI got to go back up\nagain tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.80,0:19:45.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Going back up again?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.24,0:19:47.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, putting in\nthe hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.16,0:19:48.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Tell Walker.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.60,0:19:51.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I got to start carrying\nmy sleeping bag with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.44,0:19:53.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,OK... I got two pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.36,0:19:55.88,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Three sixes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.88,0:19:58.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got\ntwo pairs of sevens\nand your other six.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.64,0:19:59.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha-ha-ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.96,0:20:03.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! I thought\nyou newspaper boys
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.04,0:20:05.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,would be a bit sharper than\nthat. What rag do you\nwrite for again?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.60,0:20:07.24,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,New York Times.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.24,0:20:09.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah, I picked\none up once.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.16,0:20:12.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You read, Ross?\nProbably stole it from\nsome derelict in the park,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.08,0:20:13.52,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,who was using it\nas a blanket.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.52,0:20:14.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I gave him a nickel!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.96,0:20:17.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't\nfind the comics,\nso I returned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.72,0:20:19.28,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get\nyour money back?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.28,0:20:21.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I ended up finishing\na pint of radiator fluid\nwith the guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.84,0:20:23.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,It was about then\nI figured it was\ntime to enlist,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.92,0:20:26.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,and here I am,\nthe best goddamn\nevac pilot in 'Nam!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.92,0:20:28.36,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell it, Ross.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.36,0:20:31.72,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Flying those choppers every\nday scrambles up your brains.\nYou get facts confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.72,0:20:33.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Ross here thinks that\nit takes some skill
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.64,0:20:35.56,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,to keep one of those\neggbeaters up in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.56,0:20:36.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Typical FAC pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.92,0:20:38.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,He labours under\nthe misapprehension
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.52,0:20:40.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,that he is the most\nSierra-Hotel cowboy\nin the Air Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.84,0:20:42.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,The real truth is,\nhe flies
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.32,0:20:44.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,a fucking VW\nMicrobus with wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.20,0:20:46.56,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this VW pilot
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.56,0:20:48.52,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,flies ten feet\noff the deck,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.52,0:20:51.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,draws fire from SAMs\ndown to eight-year-olds
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.12,0:20:52.56,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,with slingshots\nand pebbles.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.56,0:20:55.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha-ha-ha!\nA confirmation\non that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.64,0:20:56.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of times,\nI've seen Clark
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.92,0:20:58.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,return here...\nYou want one?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.48,0:20:59.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,..with leaves\nin his teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.64,0:21:00.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.68,0:21:01.72,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.72,0:21:04.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,..us black folks\nain't got no\ndepth perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.00,0:21:06.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,So we gots to fly\nwhat we gets.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.04,0:21:07.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,MEN LAUGH
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.68,0:21:10.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,They won't let us fly\nfast aeroplanes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.32,0:21:13.88,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You got to be particular\nin this man's\nAir Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.88,0:21:18.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, right here, you are\nlooking at a perfect\nflyboy profile.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.32,0:21:21.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,The kind of guy you can\ntrust when the shit\nhits the fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.84,0:21:24.72,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Boom. It's hit\nthe fan, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.12,0:21:30.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later,\nClarky.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.60,0:21:32.64,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Later, Clarky.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.64,0:21:35.92,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't wait up\nfor me, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.92,0:21:37.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.52,0:21:46.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,PLANE FLIES OVERHEAD
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.36,0:21:53.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, Bat 21.\nIs that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.72,0:21:56.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger, Bat 21.\nIt's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.96,0:22:00.88,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I need a visual reference,\nso I can stay in range.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.88,0:22:02.88,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll need one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.68,0:22:26.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Got you, Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.12,0:22:28.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Positive contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.76,0:22:38.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate\nyou dropping by,\nBirddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.32,0:22:40.72,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what\nI'm here for.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.72,0:22:46.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Charlie walked by my hole\nabout an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.12,0:22:47.92,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,How many?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.92,0:22:52.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,10 or 12. It seems\nto be quiet now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.72,0:22:54.92,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Just stay calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.92,0:22:57.56,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be out of there\nin the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.96,0:23:02.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, could you do me\na personal favour?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.32,0:23:04.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.24,0:23:06.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Get in touch\nwith my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.16,0:23:08.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I was supposed to\ncall her tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.08,0:23:10.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,She'll be\nscared to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.20,0:23:11.88,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Her name is Gwen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.88,0:23:13.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I know. I pulled\nyour personal file.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.80,0:23:15.72,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I got her address\nand number,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.72,0:23:18.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,but I think you should\nlet it ride for a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.12,0:23:19.88,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,She may not be\ntoo excited
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.88,0:23:21.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,about where you decided\nto spend the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.88,0:23:26.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we'll do it\nyour way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.28,0:23:29.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad somebody's\nthinking clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.20,0:23:32.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,How long you been flying\nOscar-Deuces?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.04,0:23:35.16,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Too long.\nDue to rotate soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.16,0:23:38.28,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I'm probably\nthe oldest captain\nin the Air Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.28,0:23:40.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,How old are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.20,0:23:42.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you believe,\n35 in June?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.64,0:23:46.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha-ha-ha!\nThat's not very old.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.40,0:23:49.36,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit.\nSometimes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.20,0:23:53.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you married,\nBirddog?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.28,0:23:56.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.00,0:23:58.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Got a wife and kid\nback home.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.52,0:24:09.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thinking about\nmy old lady a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.92,0:24:11.88,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,since I've been\ndown here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.76,0:24:16.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Funny how that works.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.12,0:24:19.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,She keeps bugging me\nthat my mind
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.00,0:24:22.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,is someplace else\nwhen I'm with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.36,0:24:26.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah,\nI know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.44,0:24:29.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Any news on the other\ncrew members?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.56,0:24:31.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,No. No other chutes\nwere spotted.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.96,0:24:33.92,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,We're still searching\nfor the wreckage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.92,0:24:35.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,The jungle is hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.32,0:24:37.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Has anyone contacted\nScott's wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.72,0:24:41.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That's been\ntaken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.12,0:24:43.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,THEY SPEAK VIETNAMESE
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.40,0:24:47.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like\na real jerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.80,0:24:50.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the big expert\non this deal,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.68,0:24:52.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,and I get us\nshot down.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.56,0:24:56.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't beat\nyourself up, Bat 21.\nIt happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.12,0:25:01.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You OK for the night,\nBat 21?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.64,0:25:06.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. No problem.\nThanks for checking in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.96,0:25:09.36,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'm RTB.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.36,0:25:11.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Tuck yourself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.32,0:25:14.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Carpool will pick you up\nat first light.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.32,0:25:18.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Birddog\nsigning off, Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.32,0:25:48.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,ENGINES IN DISTANCE
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.96,0:27:30.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, Birddog,\nthis is Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.48,0:27:32.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you\nin the vicinity?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.36,0:27:35.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger, Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.12,0:27:38.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Just about to give you\na wake-up call.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.08,0:27:40.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, take a look\nat the intersection
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.40,0:27:42.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,of hollywood and vine.\nRush-hour traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.32,0:27:44.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Could be a problem\nfor our Jolly Greens.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.72,0:27:47.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger, Bat 21.\nStand by.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.60,0:27:49.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's put some hits\non these guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.52,0:27:52.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a good visual.\nI'll call them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.60,0:27:56.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure? You're pretty\nclose to the action.\nYou might get nicked.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.04,0:27:57.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see the crossroads\nfrom here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.64,0:28:00.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,About half a click south\nof the rice paddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.04,0:28:01.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.44,0:28:04.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You pulling rank\non me, Bat 21?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.68,0:28:06.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take my chances.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.08,0:28:07.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.64,0:28:10.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.\nEnjoy the show!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.96,0:28:21.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,MEN SHOUTING/MACHINE GUNS FIRING
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.68,0:28:30.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog to Crabtree,\nI marked my targets.\nWhat are you hauling?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.84,0:28:33.08,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger, Birddog.\nThis is Crabtree,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.08,0:28:35.04,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,coming in\nfrom the south
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.04,0:28:37.16,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,with a full load\nof snake and nape.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.16,0:28:39.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger, Crabtree.\nYou see my smoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.84,0:28:41.76,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...affirmative,\nBirddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.76,0:28:43.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Waste the area,\nbut remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.64,0:28:45.56,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,we have a friendly\nin the vicinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.56,0:28:48.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Try not to ruin his day\nwith a stray frag.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.80,0:28:50.12,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.12,0:28:52.72,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,We can thread a needle\nif we have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.72,0:28:56.16,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Thread a needle,\nmy ass. Shit. Ha-ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.64,0:29:46.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog,\non your next pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.56,0:29:48.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,move just east\nof the intersection.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.92,0:29:51.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You got\ncamouflaged tanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.72,0:29:55.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger, Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.64,0:29:58.52,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Crabtree, tanks\njust east of intersection,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.52,0:30:00.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Missed on first pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.44,0:30:03.32,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger, Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.32,0:30:05.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,MACHINE GUNS FIRE
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.12,0:30:36.08,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,We're Winchester,\nBirddog. Please assess damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.08,0:30:38.40,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Additional targets\nstill appear active.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.40,0:30:41.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Copy, Crabtree.\nReturn to base.\nWill advise.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.44,0:30:47.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,MAN SHOUTS
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.16,0:30:57.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,GUNSHOT
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.76,0:31:17.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, Bat 21\nfrom Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.64,0:31:20.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, Bat 21?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.60,0:31:24.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Bat 21 from Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.00,0:31:26.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you copy, Bat 21?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.28,0:31:30.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.20,0:31:31.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You intact?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.00,0:31:36.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Affirmative.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.00,0:31:37.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice quarterbacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.40,0:31:40.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we ought to\nleave you in for\nthe second half.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.24,0:31:42.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative.\nI've seen enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.20,0:31:45.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's different\non the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.80,0:31:49.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too damn close.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.84,0:31:52.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Bat 21, your pick-up\nmay be delayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.76,0:31:55.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,The area\nis still too hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.60,0:31:58.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative! Negative! It's\ngot to be today, goddamn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.52,0:32:01.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I repeat,\narea's still too hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.80,0:32:04.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a war zone, goddamn it!\nWhat do you expect?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.20,0:32:07.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Relax, Bat 21.\nWe'll get you out\nat first light.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.60,0:32:09.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus Christ!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.00,0:32:13.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Just stay calm.\nBirddog will deliver.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.40,0:32:16.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative, Birddog.\nBat 21 has a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.52,0:32:17.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I worked it out\nlast night.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.84,0:32:20.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog would like\nto RTB, refuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.08,0:32:22.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,and confirm\nbefore you move.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.32,0:32:24.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative, Birddog.\nNot enough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.72,0:32:35.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Bat 21! Bat 21!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.40,0:32:38.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog would like to\nconfirm before you move.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.20,0:32:42.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative.\nBat's on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.60,0:32:44.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Heading\nfor the swanee.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.52,0:32:45.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Swanee?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.96,0:32:48.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Repeat, heading\nfor the swanee,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.20,0:32:50.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Like in the song.\n"Swanee, swanee.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.28,0:32:52.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,"How I love you.\nHow I love you."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.20,0:32:53.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah,\nI know the song.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.80,0:32:56.28,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,"Swanee,\nHow I Love You."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.16,0:33:01.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh. I think\nI broke the code, Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.64,0:33:03.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,But still\ndo not advise.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.24,0:33:05.28,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Route takes you through\ntoo many unfriendlies.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.28,0:33:07.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog has no way\nto track you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.08,0:33:09.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I worked out\na front nine\nto avoid the hazards.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.92,0:33:13.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Copy this.\nAdd zero to yardage.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.64,0:33:16.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Holes three, six and eight\nat Shaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.52,0:33:20.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,South one and 17\nat Macdill.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.48,0:33:24.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming in on two,\n12, 14, and 18\nat Hickum.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.80,0:33:26.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you copy?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.24,0:33:28.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Copy, but I still don't\nknow what the hell\nyou're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.00,0:33:36.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Contact Colonel Douglass\nat Kerat Air Base\nfor instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.32,0:33:40.16,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure this is\na good idea, Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.16,0:33:45.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Bat 21 is teeing off\nfrom the blue markers\nnow. Out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.80,0:33:51.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, Bat 21,\nfrom Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.20,0:33:55.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, Bat 21, Bat 21,\nfrom Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.00,0:33:57.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Bat... Oh, shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.68,0:34:18.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to\ntell me about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.00,0:34:19.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Hambleton's\nmoving on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.96,0:34:21.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's\nhe going?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.84,0:34:25.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.\nHe gave me some kind\nof goddamned code,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.00,0:34:27.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,after I decided\nit was too hot\nto pick him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.60,0:34:30.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&}- Yeah, I heard you\nbrought in the flyboys.\n{\r}\N- Mm-mmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.68,0:34:33.28,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,That was his idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.28,0:34:34.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,That's some kind of\ntough bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.96,0:34:36.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.24,0:34:38.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean,\nhe must realise
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.20,0:34:40.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,they aren't always\nthat accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.08,0:34:43.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen frags drop 30 feet\nin front of my windscreen.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.44,0:34:44.88,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.88,0:34:47.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wait, wait.\nWhere are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.20,0:34:49.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Sit down and finish\nyour beer. Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.96,0:34:52.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I got to go up again.\nI got to find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.96,0:34:55.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You're spending\nmore time in the air\nthan on Mother Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.60,0:34:57.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You look like hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.20,0:35:02.16,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I need\nthe overtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.16,0:35:05.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You are going for\na DFFC, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.00,0:35:07.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,A Distinguished\nFucking Flying Cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.92,0:35:10.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I must have\nvapour-locked,\nor something.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.80,0:35:14.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,"FAC pilot\nsaves Colonel!"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.16,0:35:16.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gearing up\nfor the ceremony.\nA full dress parade,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.56,0:35:18.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,a nice shiny medal\nto show the folks\nback home,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.96,0:35:21.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,and a newfound respect\nin the military community.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.80,0:35:24.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit! Clarky,\nstick around. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.40,0:35:25.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take\na chopper up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.96,0:35:28.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll shoot a few cows\nand have a barbecue.\nWhat do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.36,0:35:31.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Ross, not tonight, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.40,0:35:33.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think\nyou've got
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.36,0:35:36.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,a little obsessive\nbehaviour going here?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.00,0:35:39.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Obsessive behaviour?\nMe, obsessive behaviour?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.24,0:35:41.48,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I recall some of\nthe crazy, lunatic shit
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.48,0:35:42.92,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,that you've done\nin your machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.92,0:35:46.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I like hauling\nthose sorry dudes\nout of the bush.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.12,0:35:49.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I like to see their big,\nsloppy smiles when I drag them\ninto the chopper,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.36,0:35:53.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,because you just know they thought\nthey were going to spend the rest\nof the war dodging punji sticks,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.28,0:35:56.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,snakes, and gooks, and I hand them\na camel and a candy bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.32,0:35:59.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,and they smile like\nwhen they got laid\nfor the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.68,0:36:02.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not into this\ndeath-and-destruction\nbullshit either,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.08,0:36:03.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,or flying\nfucking medals.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.68,0:36:08.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, all I want to do\nis bring the old man back.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.76,0:36:13.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,OK... Go on. Get him\nthrough the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.12,0:36:16.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll haul his ass out\nin the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.52,0:36:18.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, Birddog?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.60,0:37:25.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,CLUCKING
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.16,0:38:24.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,MAN SPEAKS IN VIETNAMESE
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.76,0:38:28.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HE REPLIES IN VIETNAMESE
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.96,0:38:31.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,MAN SPEAKS ANGRILY
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.00,0:38:40.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no, no.\nLook... Friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.80,0:38:43.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HE REPEATS THE SAME WORD\nIN VIETNAMESE
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.16,0:38:48.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,< Friend. Friend.\nMAN SHOUTS ANGRILY
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.44,0:39:15.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,GUNSHOT
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.00,0:39:49.24,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Pa?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.76,0:39:54.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.24,0:40:19.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,WOMAN SOBS SOFTLY
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.44,0:41:34.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HE GROANS
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.12,0:41:54.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HE SOBS
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.16,0:42:02.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no.\nNumber 14 at Hickum.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.68,0:42:05.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Hickum.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.56,0:42:08.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the par four\nacross the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.36,0:42:10.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the one.\nHold the phone\na minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.80,0:42:12.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, Captain,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.60,0:42:15.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...number 14\nat Hickum,\n390 yards.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.60,0:42:17.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.08,0:42:19.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget\nto add the zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.00,0:42:20.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Come here, Clark.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.40,0:42:22.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel, that puts\nour puzzle together.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.36,0:42:26.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Now let's hope\nthe damn thing\nworks. ..Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.20,0:42:29.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I will\nkeep you abreast\nof everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.08,0:42:30.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.52,0:42:33.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,And thank you.\nMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.80,0:42:37.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,What have\nwe got, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.20,0:42:41.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a lot\nto tell you\nabout your boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.04,0:42:42.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like\nHambleton was flying
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.96,0:42:46.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,a pave-penny mission\nfor a major bombing\nstrike, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.32,0:42:48.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,He came up with\nthe idea himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.24,0:42:50.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,and then he\nvolunteers to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.16,0:42:52.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Right man\nfor the job\nand all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.08,0:42:54.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like to me he must have\nwritten the damn manuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.96,0:42:56.88,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't Charlie\nlike to get
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.88,0:42:59.28,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,their hands on him,\nopen him up? Shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.28,0:43:01.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't get\nany better.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.68,0:43:04.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,The strike was scheduled\nfor 07:00 hours tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.56,0:43:06.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Their objective,\ncarpet-bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.48,0:43:08.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,this crossroads\nwhere Hambleton is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.36,0:43:11.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,and everything around it\nfor 8 kilometres.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.84,0:43:14.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HE SIGHS
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.04,0:43:18.92,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what he was\ntalking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.92,0:43:21.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.04,0:43:25.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.60,0:43:29.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,They're going\nto blast the whole\ngoddamn area, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.32,0:43:31.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fucking\nblowing my brains out
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.24,0:43:32.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,trying to get\nthis motherfucker home,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.84,0:43:34.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,and they're talking\nabout carpet-bombing!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.76,0:43:36.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddamn it,\nCaptain...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.20,0:43:37.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, wait\na minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.64,0:43:39.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up,\ngoddamn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.44,0:43:44.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I bought us 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.28,0:43:46.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the best\nI could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.72,0:43:50.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Had to put\nmy ass on the line\nto get that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.08,0:43:53.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I told Seventh Air\nwe'd get him out of there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.00,0:43:55.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,That's exactly what\nwe're going to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.60,0:44:03.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice work, Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.68,0:44:05.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's don't\nstart jumping\nup and down,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.60,0:44:08.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,throwing babies\nin the air yet,\nCaptain.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.32,0:44:10.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd better\nwait and see
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.24,0:44:12.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,if Hambleton's\ncode works.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.20,0:44:14.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm. You got\nany ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.76,0:44:16.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Douglass knew\nwhat Hambleton
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.20,0:44:18.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,was talking about\nright away.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.92,0:44:20.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, they're both\ngolf fanatics.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.80,0:44:23.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,They play three times a week.\nHambleton's got a four handicap.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.72,0:44:26.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,With all that in mind, come here.\nI want to show you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.16,0:44:27.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,..Thank you, Howard.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.40,0:44:31.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Now...stay\nwith me, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.80,0:44:33.76,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,This gets\npretty wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.76,0:44:38.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Hambleton wants to get\nhere to the river,\nto the swanee, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.16,0:44:39.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, how's he\ngoing to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.44,0:44:42.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, he's not about\nto just tear ass\nout through there
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.48,0:44:43.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,and lose contact\nwith you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.80,0:44:44.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell, he's dead meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.84,0:44:47.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,On the other hand,\nhe can't get on the radio
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.20,0:44:49.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,and tell you where he's\ngoing. Charlie's got VHF too.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.32,0:44:52.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,So he gives you\nan imaginary\nnine holes of golf.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.40,0:44:54.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,When you lay those nine holes\nover our map, Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.80,0:44:58.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,there's what\nthey look like.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.28,0:45:00.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we\ncan track him,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.64,0:45:02.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,now that we know\nwhere he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.52,0:45:04.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,We know exactly where\nhe comes out at the end
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.40,0:45:06.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,because he didn't pick\nthose holes at random.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.64,0:45:08.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,They come off three\nAir Force golf courses
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.68,0:45:10.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,he's played\na hundred times,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.36,0:45:12.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,knows them like\nthe back of his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.04,0:45:13.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's take\nthese three
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.56,0:45:15.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,that come off\nShaw Air Force base.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.44,0:45:18.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,First hole, 410-yard\npar-four dogleg.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.36,0:45:20.76,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,We add that zero\nHambleton's talking about,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.76,0:45:22.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,it reads 4,100 yards,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.16,0:45:24.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,and the first green\nputs him right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.56,0:45:26.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Next green,\nhere and here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.48,0:45:30.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,These two holes\ncome off the front\nand back of Macdill.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.00,0:45:31.76,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,These four finishing\nholes here,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.76,0:45:33.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,according\nto Douglass,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.32,0:45:34.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,are the holes\nHambleton birdied
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.80,0:45:36.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,the last time\nhe played Hickum
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.56,0:45:38.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,to shoot\na one-under-par 71.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.48,0:45:40.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty good score, huh?\nHa-ha-ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.40,0:45:43.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Clever son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.04,0:45:44.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You play golf,\nCaptain?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.48,0:45:47.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,No, sir.\nGolf wasn't big\nin my neighbourhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.12,0:45:50.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.\nWell, all these holes\nare on these cards,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.00,0:45:52.88,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,and this is a glossary\nof golf terminology.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.88,0:45:55.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you're going\nto communicate\nwith Hambleton
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.72,0:45:57.76,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,using these terms,\nbecause Charlie won't know
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.76,0:45:59.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,what in the hell\nyou're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.56,0:46:01.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,until it's\ntoo late, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.04,0:46:03.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,So get busy.\nLearn this.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.40,0:46:06.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the key\nto Hambleton's code.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.64,0:46:11.56,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Dogleg.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.56,0:46:14.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Dogleg.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.40,0:46:16.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.84,0:47:24.88,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Does Anderson know\nyou borrowed his prop?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.88,0:47:25.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.92,0:47:27.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love to be there\nwhen he tries to take off.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.80,0:47:30.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to need\na hell of a long\nrunway, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.60,0:47:31.72,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.72,0:47:34.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, at\nthe risk of being\nout of line, sir,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.36,0:47:35.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you look\na bit overextended.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.96,0:47:39.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, in the best interest\nof the mission and\nyour personal safety,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.20,0:47:40.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I put together\nthis tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.60,0:47:42.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Some serious\nsounds, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.24,0:47:44.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,They're guaranteed\nto keep you alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.80,0:47:48.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You're quite a man,\nRumbaugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.00,0:47:51.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You just have\na good flight,\nall right, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.56,0:47:53.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.28,0:47:58.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,ENGINE REVS
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.00,0:48:54.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,WHISTLING
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.20,0:49:09.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.68,0:49:15.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.40,0:49:18.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,God. Wake up!\nWake up! Wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.72,0:49:21.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.40,0:49:26.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,God...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.32,0:49:44.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,SITAR MUSIC PLAYS
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.20,0:49:48.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Fucked-up\nRumbaugh shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.24,0:49:50.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,MUSIC CONTINUES
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.60,0:49:55.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog on radio.\nBat 21, this is Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.68,0:49:58.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in, come in.\nWhere the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.96,0:50:02.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog,\nthis is Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.64,0:50:04.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I read you\nloud and clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.32,0:50:05.76,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,MUSIC STOPS
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.76,0:50:09.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Copy, Bat 21. It's good\nto hear from you.\nI thought I'd lost you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.04,0:50:13.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,It's good to hear\nyour voice, Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.40,0:50:15.28,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm at\nthe third fairway,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.28,0:50:17.28,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,trying to get a fix\non your position.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.28,0:50:18.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You broke the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.72,0:50:21.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm working on it.\nIt's not an easy\ngame to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.60,0:50:23.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, what is your...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.00,0:50:27.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,..lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.04,0:50:31.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, I'm\n150 yards northwest\nof the third green.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.64,0:50:35.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you\na signal, white one.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.00,0:50:45.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Got you marked.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.04,0:50:53.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Any problems?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.24,0:50:56.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I ran into\nan unfriendly\na while back.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.08,0:50:58.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I had to do\nsome backtracking.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.48,0:51:00.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.40,0:51:02.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,My landing gear's\na little damaged,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.48,0:51:04.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's\nstill serviceable.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.20,0:51:07.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to hear\nabout that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.48,0:51:12.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Birddog...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.40,0:51:15.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,you got to get me\nout of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.28,0:51:17.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Affirmative.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.08,0:51:19.16,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here to tell you\nthe good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.16,0:51:21.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,We bought 24 hours.\nCopy that?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.96,0:51:24.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You bet I copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.60,0:51:26.48,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You must have friends\nin high places
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.48,0:51:28.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,who want to see\nyour face again.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.24,0:51:30.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,That's nice to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.60,0:51:33.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, Bat 21...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.32,0:51:35.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,stay put\nand don't transmit.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.12,0:51:37.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I have business\nto take care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.64,0:51:43.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, this is Birddog.\nThis is Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.60,0:51:46.88,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone on station?\nAnd play it cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.88,0:51:49.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,PLANE PASSES OVERHEAD
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.76,0:51:55.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Copy, Cupcake.\nIf it's not\ntoo much trouble,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.60,0:51:58.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd enjoy your company\nat coordinates
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.00,0:52:01.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Zulu-Zulu-5,\nuh, Lima-Hotel-7.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.32,0:52:03.72,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&}- MAN:{\r}\N- Cupcake\non the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.72,0:52:05.16,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Copy, Cupcake.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.16,0:52:07.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Back to you, Bat 21.\nThis is Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.40,0:52:12.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.28,0:52:17.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,..I killed\na man today.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.08,0:52:21.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.88,0:52:26.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't even\na soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.56,0:52:29.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,He just kept coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.80,0:52:31.76,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.16,0:52:37.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.72,0:52:42.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want\nto do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.80,0:52:45.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I never had to do\nanything like that\nbefore in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.88,0:52:48.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always\nbeen sitting\nin an airplane
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.80,0:52:52.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,at 30,000 feet\nwith a cup of coffee\nin front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.64,0:52:56.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Look here, Bat 21,\nI never met you,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.84,0:52:58.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,but you don't sound\nlike a killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.40,0:53:00.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you couldn't\nstop it from happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.80,0:53:04.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the important thing\nis to put it behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.88,0:53:08.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,EXPLOSION
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.88,0:53:11.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell's\ngoing on, Birddog?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.80,0:53:15.16,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,There's too many\nunfriendly foursomes\nin your vicinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.16,0:53:17.56,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Fireworks courtesy\nof Wolfpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.56,0:53:19.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,MORE EXPLOSIONS
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.00,0:53:20.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,JETS PASS OVERHEAD
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.92,0:53:25.76,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus Christ!\nDoes it ever stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.16,0:53:29.56,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you with me,\nBat 21?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.56,0:53:31.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Birddog,\nI'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.96,0:53:33.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.60,0:53:35.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you\nto listen real hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.80,0:53:38.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you're hurting,\nbut we have to deal with
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.20,0:53:40.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,getting you back\nto the clubhouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.12,0:53:43.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to\npick you up\nat first light.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.08,0:53:44.88,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, I'm ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.88,0:53:46.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,JET PASSES OVERHEAD
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.32,0:53:49.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to play\nthe fourth hole tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.20,0:53:51.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,The green\nwill be our LZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.52,0:53:56.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a long\ngoddamn hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.40,0:53:58.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. There's\na few hazards,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.32,0:54:00.28,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,but the green\nis safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.28,0:54:02.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,EXPLOSIONS CONTINUE
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.64,0:54:05.56,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Think you can\nmake it, Bat 21?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.00,0:54:09.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah,\nI should be able\nto play through.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.84,0:54:12.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking forward to\nbuying you a drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.44,0:54:15.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll start the tab.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.64,0:54:17.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.48,0:54:19.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog signing off.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.20,0:54:20.72,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll see you\nin the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.48,0:56:18.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, Bat 21, this is\nBirddog. Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.68,0:56:25.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, Bat 21.\nGo ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.08,0:56:27.48,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still\non course?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.84,0:56:32.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, yeah,\nI'm an easy chip shot
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.72,0:56:34.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,from the green,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.16,0:56:37.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,except that there's\na village right here\nin front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.60,0:56:39.92,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Reconned yesterday.\nArea's safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.92,0:56:41.88,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take\nanother look.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.88,0:56:44.76,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.96,0:56:57.68,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Shine up\nyour medal, Clarky,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.68,0:56:59.28,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm bringing back\nyour boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.28,0:57:03.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll personally\nalert Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.04,0:57:07.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Bat 21, this is Birddog\nagain. Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.40,0:57:09.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Birddog,\nI'm still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.56,0:57:11.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Not for long.\nI'm sending in\nmy best man.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.96,0:57:13.92,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Get your flares ready,\nand don't pop the smoke
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.92,0:57:17.72,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,until you hear\nfrom Jolly Greens.\nUnderstand?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.72,0:57:19.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger, Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.72,0:57:34.04,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&}- WALKER:{\r}\N- Bat 21,\nCobra Leader.\nDo you copy?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.48,0:57:37.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.12,0:57:39.76,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll come over\nyour position\nfrom the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.76,0:57:42.24,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Be ready to pop\nthose flares.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.24,0:57:44.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been ready\nfor two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.12,0:58:06.24,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold what you got,\nBig Sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.24,0:58:09.04,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to send Birddog in\nto take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.04,0:58:11.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.92,0:58:27.00,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk to me,\nBirddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.00,0:58:29.36,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.36,0:58:33.04,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going in\nfor a closer look.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.04,0:58:36.36,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go.\nBe right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.40,0:58:58.44,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,It don't look\nlike anybody's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.48,0:59:14.80,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, Big Sky,\ngo get him.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.80,0:59:17.08,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll cover your tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.64,0:59:29.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Jolly Green\nfrom Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.20,0:59:31.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You're looking good,\nlooking good.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.64,0:59:34.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming in on your LZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.24,0:59:43.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,SHOUTING IN VIETNAMESE
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.40,0:59:53.08,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit! We're taking hits.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.08,0:59:57.68,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,The village is hot!\nThe village is hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.68,1:00:00.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, there's\nat least two machine guns\nin the village!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.84,1:00:04.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you said\nthat goddamn LZ\nwas secure!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.48,1:00:07.48,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Get back in the trees, Bat 21.\nBack in the trees!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.24,1:00:19.44,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Stevie, open up.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.96,1:00:39.64,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Get those mines ready.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.64,1:00:41.96,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to drop them\nright here in this paddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.96,1:00:43.68,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep them away\nfrom Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.88,1:01:02.04,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Drop those mines!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.72,1:01:12.60,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.56,1:01:19.48,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Sky,\nget the hell out of there.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.48,1:01:21.96,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming back.\nOpen up, Steven.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.76,1:01:26.68,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Get on those guns\nand give them hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.44,1:01:38.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Agh!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.48,1:01:40.56,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a bitch!\nHe's hit!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.56,1:01:43.16,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of him.\nHendricks,\nget on the gun!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.16,1:01:44.88,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to\nfix you up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.88,1:01:47.24,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Sky,\nabort mission.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.24,1:01:50.20,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Repeat, abort! Abort!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.76,1:01:54.48,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Boys, they're not\ngoing to stick a fork\nin me till I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.48,1:01:55.88,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to get\nthat boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.88,1:01:58.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Abort mission, Big Sky!\nGet the hell out of there, Ross!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.44,1:02:00.68,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. Transmission\nis breaking up.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.68,1:02:02.76,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Repeat, abort!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.76,1:02:05.32,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. Transmission\nis breaking up.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.32,1:02:07.92,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,That's bullshit!\nYou heard me!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.92,1:02:09.96,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I said abort!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.60,1:02:19.96,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck it.\nLet's go in.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.88,1:02:26.32,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, you...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.00,1:02:36.16,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Ross,\nget out of there!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.68,1:02:42.32,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.32,1:02:46.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,He's hit!\nBirddog, he's hit!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.44,1:02:48.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.48,1:02:53.48,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit! I'm losing it!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.92,1:03:07.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Up, Big Sky!\nBig Rocks! Pull out!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.80,1:03:09.28,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit.\nWe're going down.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.28,1:03:11.92,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going down.\nMayday! Mayday!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.60,1:03:21.84,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see\na goddamn thing,\ngoddamn it!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.84,1:03:24.20,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going down.\nMayday.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.88,1:03:50.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HE COUGHS
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.52,1:03:52.00,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Start, motherfucker!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.00,1:03:53.88,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,MEN SHOUT
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.88,1:03:54.92,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Start!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.92,1:03:56.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get\nout of here, Ross!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.68,1:03:59.48,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck!\nThey're coming!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.48,1:04:02.08,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,The gun jammed!\nLet's go, Ross! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.08,1:04:05.60,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddamn it!\nLet's fucking go!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.60,1:04:08.28,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Start! Shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.28,1:04:10.68,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Start!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.68,1:04:12.32,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.32,1:04:15.32,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Pearson.\nWe got to get\nout of here.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.32,1:04:16.80,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Ross!\nJesus! The gun!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.80,1:04:19.28,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! We got to get\nout of here!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.28,1:04:21.00,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddamn it, come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.00,1:04:22.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,GUNFIRE
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.80,1:04:24.60,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Agh!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.60,1:04:26.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Get up, man!\nWe got to go!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.84,1:04:28.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Aah!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.12,1:04:38.40,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Finley, goddamn it!\nGive me the gun!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.40,1:04:40.88,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit! Come on,\ngive me the gun, Finley!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.88,1:04:43.80,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me the goddamn gun,\ngoddamn it!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.80,1:04:47.00,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus Christ!\nDon't shoot!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.00,1:04:49.72,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't shoot!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.72,1:04:52.00,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't shoot!\nHoly shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.00,1:04:55.24,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fuckin' hit, man!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.24,1:04:57.20,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus Christ!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.20,1:04:59.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.12,1:05:04.00,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Steve, stay alive!\nSomeone will be back.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.00,1:05:06.20,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't fuckin'\nleave us, Ross!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.20,1:05:09.72,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Just stay alive,\ngoddamn it!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.72,1:05:12.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,SHOUTING IN VIETNAMESE
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.68,1:05:18.24,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't leave\nus, Ross!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.24,1:05:20.60,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.\nI'll be back.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.60,1:05:23.32,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.32,1:05:25.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,SHOUTING CONTINUES
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.04,1:05:30.20,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Ross! Ross!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.20,1:05:32.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,GUNFIRE
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.64,1:05:35.00,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddamn you!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.88,1:06:27.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, they've got\ntwo of our men.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.20,1:06:30.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the rest\nof the crew is dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.12,1:06:32.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, copy, Bat 21.\nStand by.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.04,1:06:34.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Cobra Leader, Charlie\nhas two of our airmen.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.08,1:06:35.88,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you identify?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.88,1:06:39.24,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative, Birddog.\nCan't make out from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.24,1:06:41.64,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,We're holding\nour fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.64,1:06:45.32,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,They shot\nmy damn hydraulics out.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.32,1:06:48.88,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to be able\nto put this thing down here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.88,1:06:50.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going down\nfor a closer look.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.76,1:06:52.20,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Not advisable, Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.20,1:06:54.28,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,It will be\na quick pass.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.64,1:07:02.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,GUNFIRE
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.32,1:07:06.92,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Confirmed, two airmen.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.92,1:07:09.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,One is pilot.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.12,1:07:21.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,THEY SPEAK IN VIETNAMESE
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.32,1:07:25.84,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what, Charlie?\nI don't follow\nyour fucking drift.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.84,1:07:28.24,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,I took Spanish\nin school.\nNo comprendo.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.24,1:07:30.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HE SHOUTS IN VIETNAMESE
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.40,1:07:34.48,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Get your fucking slimy\nfucking hands off me!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.84,1:07:40.56,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what the fuck\nyou're talking about!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.56,1:07:43.08,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't\nunderstand you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.08,1:07:47.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, they're\ntrying to get him\nto tell where I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.28,1:07:49.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Copy, Bat 21.\nJust stay low.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.44,1:08:03.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,GUNSHOT
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.40,1:08:05.68,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard! Motherfucker!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.04,1:08:21.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,They just killed\none of our men.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.52,1:08:24.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it the pilot,\nBat 21?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.20,1:08:26.76,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so.\nIt's me they want.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.76,1:08:28.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to give\nmyself up.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.92,1:08:31.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your ass down, Bat 21!\nCharlie doesn't bargain.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.68,1:08:33.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing you can\ndo about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.44,1:08:36.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, retreat double-time\nback into the trees.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.20,1:09:01.48,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, fella.\nCome closer.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.48,1:09:03.68,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Come on,\nyou motherfucker.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.68,1:09:05.60,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.60,1:09:07.52,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.52,1:09:09.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HE IMITATES AN EXPLOSION
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.40,1:09:11.88,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.88,1:09:14.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,They're walking him\nout into the minefield.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.68,1:09:16.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.96,1:09:21.92,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.76,1:10:02.64,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.64,1:10:03.68,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Agh!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.04,1:10:07.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,ROSS SCREAMS
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.40,1:10:10.92,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Aah! Aah!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.92,1:10:14.12,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddamn it!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.36,1:10:26.44,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Aah!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.00,1:10:41.96,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Motherfucker!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.96,1:10:47.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You lowlife...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.72,1:11:06.88,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got\nenough dead heroes\nfor one day, Clark!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.88,1:11:09.28,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Get your ass\nout of there!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.28,1:11:11.48,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, fuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.16,1:11:19.84,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll get Bat 21\nback on the course!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.84,1:11:24.32,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Then rendezvous with me\nat Hilo-1-8-5.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.32,1:11:27.28,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to waste\nthis whole goddamned area!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.28,1:11:42.08,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Four-square leader,\nhustle your ass over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.08,1:11:45.76,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,One click north\nof Hilo-1-niner-6.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.76,1:11:48.16,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Gun emplacement\nin village.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.16,1:11:52.44,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Jolly Green down.\nCrew is dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.44,1:11:55.44,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Look for the smoke.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.60,1:12:01.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,People are still\nin the village.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.56,1:12:03.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Charlie is using them\nfor cover.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.48,1:12:05.88,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay off\nfrequency, Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.88,1:12:08.24,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Await instructions\nfrom Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.52,1:12:18.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog. Birddog,\npeople are in the village.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.36,1:12:22.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Repeat, civilians,\nwomen and children,\nin the village.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.04,1:12:24.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a confirmation.\nWill advise.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.52,1:12:29.16,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Cobra Leader,\nthis is Birddog.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.16,1:12:30.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Village is still\nnot clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.68,1:12:32.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Civilians\nstill in area.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.20,1:12:34.84,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay off frequency.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.84,1:12:37.04,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Delay the strike.\nRepeat, delay strike.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.04,1:12:40.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Bat 21,\nget back on course.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.32,1:12:42.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Will connect\nwith you at swanee.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.04,1:12:44.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck the goddamn swanee.\nDelay the strike!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.96,1:12:46.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,That was my friend\nlaying in the mud
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.64,1:12:48.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,with his fucking head\nblown off!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.40,1:12:49.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, get back\non course!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.80,1:12:52.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, do as I say!\nBack on course!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.32,1:13:55.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,People keep dying\nall around me.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.00,1:14:02.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm through killing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.84,1:14:06.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm through,\ngoddamn it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.80,1:14:53.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HE SIGHS
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.12,1:14:58.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You called\nfor me, sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.84,1:15:03.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahem...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.32,1:15:05.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Lost six people\ntoday, Clark.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.72,1:15:08.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Kids, all of them,\njust kids.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.00,1:15:12.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,And I couldn't\nguarantee
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.32,1:15:13.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,we'd get him\nout of there
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.80,1:15:15.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,if we had another week.\nDamn it, it's too hot.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.56,1:15:18.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HE SIGHS
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.60,1:15:21.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,So, the strike\nis a go...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.96,1:15:24.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,07:00 hours\ntomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.36,1:15:27.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,They're\ngoing to level\nthe whole area.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.24,1:15:29.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,All we can do is\nhope and pray to God
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.64,1:15:32.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Hambleton makes it\nto the river.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.52,1:15:34.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.40,1:15:37.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I ever\ncall the Navy,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.28,1:15:39.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,and, uh, they're\ngoing to send
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.72,1:15:41.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,a patrol boat\nup there.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.56,1:15:45.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you\nheaded?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.92,1:15:49.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to help him\nmake it to the river, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.08,1:15:53.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Planes are\ngrounded, Clark.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.12,1:15:55.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,We are not to go\nback in there
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.84,1:15:57.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,until the strike\nis over.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.04,1:16:01.76,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Our hands\nare tied.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.76,1:16:03.72,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.16,1:16:17.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HE SIGHS
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.16,1:17:05.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, Bat 21. Over.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.96,1:17:10.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Birddog, Bat 21.\nHow do you read? Over.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.32,1:17:13.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,'Birddog, this is Bat 21.\nCome in.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.68,1:17:16.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,'I'm on the sixth hole, Birddog.\nDo you copy?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.56,1:17:19.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,'Birddog,\nthis is Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.40,1:17:22.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,'Come in, Birddog.'
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.60,1:18:27.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.88,1:18:44.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,For me?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.16,1:18:49.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,BOY SPEAKS IN VIETNAMESE
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.92,1:21:06.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Definitely not\na good idea, sir.\nIt's a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.24,1:21:08.16,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I trained in one\nof these things\n15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.16,1:21:10.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,So, just refresh\nmy memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.12,1:21:11.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You got\nthree minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.92,1:21:16.80,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go,\nRumbaugh.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.80,1:21:18.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.16,1:21:19.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.28,1:21:21.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your rotor speed.\nKeep it in the green.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.60,1:21:23.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,This is\nyour engine speed.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.04,1:21:24.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it also\nin the green.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.52,1:21:26.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Red-line and you\ncrash and burn.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.36,1:21:28.76,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, pedals.\nPedals work the same\nas your ship.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.76,1:21:30.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,The stick does not.\nIt's cyclic.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.72,1:21:32.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,It controls the angles\nof your blades, all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.80,1:21:35.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe\nyou're taking\nthe old man's ship.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.52,1:21:38.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, power.\nPower's controlled\nby your collective.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.20,1:21:39.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,One thing you may\nhave forgotten is,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.68,1:21:42.20,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,when you increase power,\nyou increase left pedal
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.20,1:21:45.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,to compensate for\nincreased torque.\nGot it?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.56,1:21:49.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, um...yeah,\nit's coming back to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.40,1:21:52.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,And what about\nautorotation?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.00,1:21:53.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? You planning\non not coming back, sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.84,1:21:56.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.60,1:22:00.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.\nYour engine quits.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.12,1:22:01.36,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You're falling out\nof the sky.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.36,1:22:05.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, all you've got left\nis the energy stored\nin your blades, OK?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.32,1:22:06.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Push the left...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.92,1:22:10.12,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,No, push the right,\nthe right pedal\nto the floor,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.12,1:22:11.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,collective down,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.84,1:22:13.96,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,keep your rotor speed\nin the green.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.96,1:22:17.84,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it at about 80 knots\nand about 100 feet\noff the deck.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.84,1:22:20.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Begin to flare and then\ncushion it on down\nwith the collective.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.64,1:22:23.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you may\nstart to spin,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.04,1:22:25.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,but that's cool.\nDon't panic.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.28,1:22:27.40,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Key point being,\nhe who hesitates...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.40,1:22:29.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to\nhesitate, all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.32,1:22:30.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.76,1:22:33.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's your checklist,\nyour maps,\nall your golf shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.60,1:22:35.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.04,1:22:36.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you got\neverything, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.48,1:22:38.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You understand\nall this?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.04,1:22:39.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.08,1:22:40.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.32,1:22:41.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks\nfor the lesson.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.76,1:22:42.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Just come back,\nall right?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.72,1:23:01.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Pedals! Pedals!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.44,1:23:05.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Collective!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.28,1:23:07.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.16,1:23:09.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Up! Up! Up!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.24,1:23:15.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, all right.\nTorque, torque, torque.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.24,1:23:20.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Get it up!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.00,1:23:23.52,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You got it!\nYou got it! Up!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.00,1:23:38.84,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that crazy\nson of a bitch?!\nIs that Clark?!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.84,1:23:41.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe\nit is, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.08,1:23:44.04,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.04,1:23:46.64,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,We're looking at\na court-martial now!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.64,1:23:48.56,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Rotor speed up.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.56,1:23:50.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Throttle friction.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.44,1:23:56.24,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus Christ!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.24,1:23:58.64,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,When he gets\nback here, Sergeant,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.64,1:24:00.56,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm throwing his ass\nin the stockade!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.56,1:24:02.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have\na stockade, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.32,1:24:04.24,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll build one!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.24,1:24:06.68,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.04,1:24:16.48,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.00,1:24:35.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, all right,\nall right, here I come.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.24,1:25:16.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Chopper Pilot,\nthis is Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.64,1:25:18.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,This is\nChopper Pilot,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.08,1:25:20.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,above your signal\non the ninth hole.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.44,1:25:21.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you,\nBirddog?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.92,1:25:23.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.44,1:25:25.24,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's get you\nout of here.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.24,1:25:27.64,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,50 metres east\nof you, there's\na small field.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.64,1:25:30.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can get\ninto it, I can\nmake it happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.12,1:25:32.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Copy that, Bat 21?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.00,1:25:34.44,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm on my way,\nBirddog.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.44,1:26:25.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,THEY SPEAK IN VIETNAMESE
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.04,1:26:53.88,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Down!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.48,1:27:11.80,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,- Let's go!\N{\1c&H00FFFF&}- OK!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.64,1:27:23.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.68,1:27:25.28,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.08,1:27:39.60,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.24,1:27:49.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.28,1:27:56.88,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to see you,\nBirddog.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.60,1:28:02.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat, Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.84,1:28:10.56,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better\ncheck the charts.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.56,1:28:13.16,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I had\na hell of a time\nnavigating here.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.96,1:28:18.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,GUNFIRE
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.48,1:28:19.88,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.64,1:28:25.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.24,1:28:33.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You're losing\noil pressure.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.16,1:28:35.00,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.00,1:28:41.12,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,There's the river.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.12,1:28:42.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,We got to make it\nfrom here.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.68,1:28:45.52,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going\nto have to put\nthis baby down, OK?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.12,1:28:50.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a clearing\nat 9 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.04,1:29:27.68,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut into the woods!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.48,1:29:31.48,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,GUNFIRE
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.84,1:29:40.44,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.60,1:30:01.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,It's\nthe air strike.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.00,1:30:04.28,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,It's right\non time.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.28,1:30:05.32,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.96,1:30:08.72,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,SHOUTING IN VIETNAMESE
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.92,1:30:17.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Move!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.24,1:31:28.36,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, shit!\nGoddamn!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.16,1:33:17.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,COUGHING
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.80,1:34:15.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I've been\nin the service...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.64,1:34:18.08,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,most of my adult life.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.88,1:34:23.32,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the first time\nI ever saw any war.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.72,1:34:28.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I was\na little closer\nto the action.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.60,1:34:30.04,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Aah...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.04,1:34:34.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I've wanted to be\na fighter pilot\nsince I was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.84,1:34:37.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,But they\nwouldn't let me\nout of the O-2.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.36,1:34:40.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucky for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.28,1:34:49.24,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,You could have\nquit anytime.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.64,1:34:52.56,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you keep\ncoming back?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.00,1:34:56.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess it's\nthe stubborn\nside of me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.84,1:34:59.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I started out\njust doing my job,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.76,1:35:01.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,no different\nfrom you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.08,1:35:05.68,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate being told\nI can't do something.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.68,1:35:09.40,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's why\nI'm still a captain.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.28,1:35:13.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.20,1:35:16.60,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I started feeling\nwhat you were\ngoing through.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.00,1:35:20.76,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard it\nin your voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.56,1:35:29.04,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,DISTANT RUMBLING
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.92,1:35:45.56,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,We're home free,\nColonel.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.24,1:35:49.16,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.16,1:35:50.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,HE SIGHS
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.00,1:35:54.88,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut the Colonel\ncrap, OK, Birddog?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.88,1:35:57.76,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,It's\nIceal Hambleton.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.76,1:35:59.20,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Iceal?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.20,1:36:00.64,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha-ha-ha!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.64,1:36:02.08,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha-ha-ha!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.08,1:36:04.00,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Hamb.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.00,1:36:07.84,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Hey...\nClark Bartholomew.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.84,1:36:09.28,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,Bartholomew?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.28,1:36:10.72,s3,,0000,0000,0000,,Clarky.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.72,1:36:12.92,s0,,0000,0000,0000,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.92,1:36:32.04,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&}- MAN ON RADIO:\n{\r}\N- This is USPB-Niner-6.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.04,1:36:34.68,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,We have your boys aboard.\nInjuries have been treated.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.68,1:36:36.96,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,Will rendezvous with you\nat base Victor-4.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.96,1:36:39.48,s2,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Niner-6 out.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.48,1:36:41.88,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&HFFFFFF&}- WALKER:\n{\r}\N- Welcome home, Bat 21.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.88,1:36:44.76,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you and the Captain\nmeet me at the 19th hole?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.76,1:36:46.68,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,The drinks are on me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.68,1:36:49.60,s1,,0000,0000,0000,,Cobra Leader,\nover and out.

